   "source": [
    "# Simulation de Quantum Physical Unclonable Functions (QPUF)\n",
    "\n",
    "Ce notebook explore la génération de la matrice de scattering $H$ et la distribution de ses valeurs propres,\n",
    "tel que décrit dans le document PSC DZB, basé sur l'article :\n",
    "\n",
    "> Goorden *et al.*, \"Quantum-secure authentication of a physical unclonable key\", *Optica* **1**, 421–424 (2014).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Plan du notebook :**\n",
    "1. Paramètres et imports\n",
    "2. Génération de la matrice de scattering $H$ (unitaire et non-unitaire)\n",
    "3. Distribution des valeurs propres dans $\\mathbb{C}$ en fonction de $\\sigma$\n",
    "4. Analyses spectrales avancées (rayon spectral, valeurs singulières, espacement, conditionnement)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "93c85475",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Imports et paramètres"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "1edf248a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
    "    'figure.facecolor': '#fafafa',\n",
    "    'axes.facecolor': '#fafafa',\n",
    "    'font.size': 12,\n",
    "    'figure.dpi': 100,\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "N = 1600\n",
    "n = 5\n",
    "eta = 0.5\n",
    "lambda_dc = 0.01\n",
    "runs = 1000\n",
    "threshold = 2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f0610bbb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Génération de la matrice de scattering $H$\n",
    "\n",
    "Deux cas sont considérés :\n",
    "- **Unitaire** : on construit $H$ via la décomposition QR d'une matrice gaussienne complexe. Les valeurs propres sont toutes de module 1.\n",
    "- **Non-unitaire** : $H = \\frac{\\sigma}{\\sqrt{2N}}(X + iY)$ avec $X, Y \\sim \\mathcal{N}(0, I_N)$. On normalise ensuite par le rayon spectral multiplié par $1/\\alpha$ pour garantir $|\\lambda_{\\max}| = \\alpha < 1$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "7ea9b04b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Unitaire    — rayon spectral : 1.000000\n",
      "Non-unitaire — rayon spectral : 0.950000 (cible α=0.95)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def generate_scattering_matrix(N, unitary=False, sigma=1.0, alpha=0.95):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Génère une matrice de scattering NxN.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters\n",
    "    ----------\n",
    "    N : int – nombre de modes spatiaux\n",
    "    unitary : bool – si True, retourne une matrice unitaire (QR)\n",
    "    sigma : float – écart-type des coefficients gaussiens (partie réelle et imaginaire)\n",
    "    alpha : float in (0,1) – rayon spectral cible pour le cas non-unitaire\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    H = (sigma / np.sqrt(2 * N)) * (np.random.randn(N, N) + 1j * np.random.randn(N, N))\n",
    "\n",
    "    if unitary:\n",
    "        Q, _ = np.linalg.qr(H)\n",
    "        return Q\n",
    "\n",
    "    eigvals = np.linalg.eigvals(H)\n",
    "    rho = np.max(np.abs(eigvals))\n",
    "    H = alpha * H / rho\n",
    "    return H\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "H_unitary = generate_scattering_matrix(N, unitary=True)\n",
    "H_nonunitary = generate_scattering_matrix(N, unitary=False, sigma=1.0, alpha=0.95)\n",
    "\n",
    "eigvals_u = np.linalg.eigvals(H_unitary)\n",
    "eigvals_nu = np.linalg.eigvals(H_nonunitary)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Unitaire    — rayon spectral : {np.max(np.abs(eigvals_u)):.6f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Non-unitaire — rayon spectral : {np.max(np.abs(eigvals_nu)):.6f} (cible α=0.95)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "445ae365",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Distribution des valeurs propres dans $\\mathbb{C}$\n",
    "\n",
    "On génère $H$ **sans normalisation spectrale** (pour observer le disque naturel) pour différentes variances $\\sigma^2$. D'après la **loi circulaire de Girko**, les valeurs propres de $\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{N}}G$ (avec $G$ i.i.d. complexe gaussien) se répartissent uniformément dans un disque de rayon $\\sigma$."
   ]
  },
