    "## 5. Protocole d'authentification : base de données\n",
    "\n",
    "Pour un $H$ donné, on construit $N$ paires $(C_k, y_k)$ :\n",
    "- $y_k = (0, \\dots, 1, \\dots, 0)^T$ (vecteur cible, 1 en position $k$)\n",
    "- $C_k = \\frac{H^\\dagger y_k}{\\|H^\\dagger y_k\\|}$ (challenge normalisé)\n",
    "\n",
    "On construit la BDD pour les **deux cas** : $H$ unitaire et $H$ non-unitaire."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "sec5_funcs",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def compute_challenge(H, yk):\n",
    "    C = H.conj().T @ yk\n",
    "    return C / np.linalg.norm(C)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_database(H):\n",
    "    Nh = H.shape[0]\n",
    "    challenges = []\n",
    "    for k in range(Nh):\n",
    "        yk = np.zeros(Nh, dtype=complex)\n",
    "        yk[k] = 1.0\n",
    "        challenges.append(compute_challenge(H, yk))\n",
    "    return challenges\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def propagate(H, C):\n",
    "    return H @ C\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def photon_detection(y, n, eta, lambda_dc):\n",
    "    mu = eta * n * np.abs(y)**2 + lambda_dc\n",
    "    return np.random.poisson(mu)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def camera_frame(counts):\n",
    "    Nc = len(counts)\n",
    "    L = int(np.sqrt(Nc))\n",
    "    return counts[:L*L].reshape((L, L))"
   ]
  },
